                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>66. W. 128<hi rend="sup">th</hi> st<lb/>
                N. Y. Feb<hi rend="sup">ry</hi> 23<hi rend="sup">rd</hi>&#47;88<lb/></p>
            <p>My dear Mr <sic>Morrais</sic><lb/></p>
            <p>I write thus again<lb/> to you and I will not<lb/> ask you to pardon my<lb/> importunity because I<lb/> am well aware that you<lb/> are tireless in your efforts<lb/> to promote the cause of<lb/> Israsel.  Our Fair will<lb/> soon take place&#44; and<lb/> altho we have tried our<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>very best we have not<lb/> as yet been very success<lb/><del>s</del>ful.  You recollect you<lb/> kindly introduced me<lb/> to Mr A. Marcus of Boston<lb/> who responded favorably<lb/> by saying he would<lb/> donate to our Fair&#44; he<lb/> has not done so as<lb/> yet&#44; and I am fearful<lb/> that in the press of<lb/> &#91;&#63;&#93; &#38;c he has forgotten<lb/> us.  I would like you<lb/> please to advise me<lb/> <sic>wether</sic> to write him<lb/> again or not&#44; I enclosed<lb/> him a Circular two<lb/> months ago but he<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="3"/>
            <p>has not acknowledged<lb/> it&#44; It would have gratified<lb/> you&#44; to have been present<lb/> at the examination of<lb/> our school last Sunday<lb/> about 125 children taken<lb/> from the poorest classes<lb/> so orderly&#44; so perfect<lb/> in Hebrew and the<lb/> <del>Phal</del> elements of our Faith.<lb/> when two or three years<lb/> ago&#44; they were ignorant<lb/> little street children.<lb/>  It is for that school too<lb/> we require funds&#44; it has<lb/> grown so we must<lb/> increase our schools rooms<lb/> &#38;c&#44; I am taking up too<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="4"/>
            <p>much of your time I am<lb/> <sic>afail</sic> but I am so very<lb/> anxious to be the means<lb/> of doing some good. <del>more</del><lb/> for it is only now that<lb/> time and <sic>oppertunity</sic><lb/> has been given to me to do<lb/> so&#44; I will conclude with<lb/> best wishes for you and<lb/> your circle&#44;<lb/> I remain yours<lb/> truly S N. Carr<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="5"/>
            <p>&#34;Congregation Moses Montefiore&#44;&#34;<lb/>
                &#40;SPANISH AND PORTUGUESE&#41;<lb/>
                NO. 529 EAST 86TH STREET&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>New York&#44; January 1st&#44; 1888.<lb/></p>
            <p>To Mr. <del>Whitney</del>&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>The undersigned Executive Committee of a Fair projected in aid of the building<lb/> fund of the Spanish and Portuguese Congregation Moses Montefiore of the City of New<lb/> York&#44; respectfully ask your co&#45;operation and support in the task which they have<lb/> undertaken.<lb/></p>
            <p>The Congregation Moses Montefiore has been in existence since the year 1883&#44;<lb/> and has held divine services and kept a religious school&#42; during that period&#44; but has<lb/> always met with drawbacks and experienced no little inconvenience from the fact that<lb/> it does not own a house of worship.  The few who have generously given of their means<lb/> to keep this Congregation alive&#44; cannot&#44; without your assistance&#44; extend its usefulness&#44; or<lb/> feel assured of future success.<lb/></p>
            <p>The Congregation bears the widely known name of one of the noblest and best<lb/> of men that ever lived&#44; and in erecting a suitable house of prayer we believe that we<lb/> fitly perpetuate his piety and good deeds.<lb/></p>
            <p>It is proposed to build a synagogue of moderate dimensions&#44; always keeping in<lb/> view&#44; however&#44; the increasing attendance at the religious school.<lb/></p>
            <p>Contributions may be sent to any member of the Executive or Honorary Executive<lb/> Committees&#44; who will duly acknowledge the same.<lb/></p>
            <p>The Fair will be held at Webster Hall&#44; No. &#91;...&#93; 11th Street&#44; and will be opened<lb/> on March 5th&#44; 1888&#44; for a period of seven days.<lb/></p>
            <p>Respectfully yours&#44;<lb/>
                A. M. LAREDO&#44; Chairman&#44; 31 Broadway&#44;<lb/>
                G. S. ROSENBERG&#44; Louisville&#44; Kentucky&#44;<lb/>
                DR. A. E. HARTOGENSIS&#44; Treasurer&#44; 208 E. 49th St.&#44;	<emph rend="italics">Executive</emph><lb/>
                A. PARIENTE&#44; 250 East 90th Street&#44;			<emph rend="italics">Committee</emph>.<lb/>
                REV. MOSES A. GUEDALIA&#44; 231 East 81st Street&#44;<lb/>
                ISIDORE OSORIO&#44; Secretary&#44; 319 Broadway&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>D. M. PIZA&#44; Treasurer&#44; 24 State Street&#44;<lb/>
                JULIUS J. LYONS&#44; 140 Nassau Street&#44;	<emph rend="italics">Honorary</emph><lb/>
                REV. H. P. MENDES&#44; 27 West 16th Street&#44;	<emph rend="italics">Executive Committee</emph>.<lb/>
                REV. A. H. NIETO&#44; 256 West 22d Street&#44;<lb/></p>
                
            <p>&#42;One hundred and twenty&#45;five children now receive instruction at this school&#44; but with increased <sic>accomodations</sic><lb/> this number can be easily doubled.<lb/></p>
